The paper deals with natural language processing and specifically with word sense disambiguation, which is a subfield of computational linguistics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses game theory and machine learning techniques, which are common in the subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with graph theory and optimization, which are relevant to the subfield of computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper uses similarity measures and semantic information, which are relevant to the subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). However, since the paper focuses more on natural language processing and machine learning, the subfields of computational linguistics and artificial intelligence are more likely.
